The paper investigates the degree of consensus within the software engineering academic community concerning members' implicit theories of software engineering, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The use of diagrams to represent personal understanding of causal relationships between core software engineering constructs suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social informatics (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the importance of evidence-based practice, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
